$ PHP code snippets: the urldecode() function

`urldecode()` can be used to decode *percent encoded* characters of an → development/web/URI-URL-URN-IRI-URC#uri[URI].

The following example tries to demonstrate that the values in the super global → development/web/php/snippets/array/associative[associative array] → development/web/php/snippets/_GET[`$_GET`] is already url-decoded, but
not the the value of `→ development/web/php/snippets/_SERVER[$_SERVER]['QUERY_STRING']`.

